 <purpose>

This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the definition of base elements of representations.  
<p>   
This edition incorporates modifications of the previous edition. 
</p><p>
The following ARM EXPRESS declarations have been modified:</p>
<ul><li>
Representation;
</li><li>
Representation_item.
</li></ul>
<p>The following ARM EXPRESS declarations have been added:</p>
<ul><li>
Numerical_representation_context;
</li><li>
Representation_relationship;
</li><li>
String_representation_item.
</li></ul>
<p>The definitions of the following ARM EXPRESS data types have been modified:</p>
<ul><li>
Representation;
</li><li>
Representation_context;
</li><li>
Representation_item.
</li></ul>
<p>In addition, modifications have been made to the mapping specification, the MIM schema and the EXPRESS-G diagrams to reflect and be consistent with the modifications of the ARM.</p>
 </purpose>

 <inscope>
<li>definition of a context of representation;</li>
<li>definition of a kind of representation context suitable for the specification of numerical values;</li>
<li>definition of a representation;</li>
<li>definition of a relationship between two representations;</li>
<li>definition of an element of representation;</li>
<!--  <li>definition of a compound element of representation;</li>	-->
<li>definition of a text as an element of representation.</li>
 </inscope>

 <outscope>
   <li>identification of the property with which the representation is associated;</li>
   <li>any presentation aspects of a representation;</li>
   <li>definition of representations for specific purposes.</li>
 </outscope>

